    public override async Task SeedAsync()
    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Announcements Admin",
            Slug = "announcements-admin-overview",
            Summary = "How admins and managers send company announcements: the Admin > Announcements panel, sending a new announcement (severity, scope, acknowledgment, expiry), the sent-announcements list and acknowledgment roster, and reusable templates.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/admin/announcements"]""",
            Tags = """["announcements","admin","communication","broadcast"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Announcements Admin\n\nAnnouncements are official messages that admins and managers send to the company. Unlike a chat message, an announcement is targeted and trackable: you choose who sees it, how urgent it is, whether people must confirm they saw it, and when it expires. People see it as a banner the moment you send it, and you can check exactly who has confirmed it.\n\nThis panel is the single place to **send** announcements, **review** everything you have sent, see **who confirmed** each one, and manage reusable **templates**. (Announcements are not written in Chat. The Chat broadcast channel shows them, but you write and manage them here, in Admin.)\n\n### Finding the panel\n\nGo to **Admin → Announcements**. The panel has two tabs:\n\n- **Announcements** — the list of everything you have sent, with its New Announcement button.\n- **Templates** — reusable announcement drafts, with its New Template button.\n\nWho can do what: sending announcements and viewing the sent list and confirmations is for **Admins and Managers**; creating and deleting **templates** is for **Admins**.\n\n### Sending a new announcement\n\nFrom the **Announcements** tab, click **New Announcement** to open the send window. Fill in:\n\n- **Template** (optional) — pick a saved template to fill in the message, urgency, audience, and confirm setting. You can then edit anything before sending.\n- **Title** (required, up to 200 characters) — the headline people see.\n- **Content** (required, up to 5,000 characters) — the body of the message.\n- **Severity** (required) — how urgent it is: **Info**, **Warning**, or **Critical**. This sets the label color and signals urgency.\n- **Scope** (required) — who gets it (see below).\n- **Target Teams** — shown only when you send to specific teams; pick one or more teams.\n- **Expires At** (optional) — a date after which the announcement stops showing. Leave blank for no expiry.\n- **Require Acknowledgment** — an on/off switch. When on, people must confirm they saw it, and you can see who did.\n\nClick **Send**. The announcement goes to its audience right away and appears at the top of the sent list.\n\n### Scope — who receives it\n\nScope controls the audience:\n\n- **Company-Wide** — everyone in the company.\n- **Selected Teams** — members of one or more teams you pick.\n- **Individual Team** — a single team you pick.\n- **Team Leads Only** — only managers and admins across the whole company, not every member. There is no team to pick; it always goes to all managers and admins.\n\nWhen you choose **Selected Teams** or **Individual Team**, a **Target Teams** picker appears so you can choose which teams the announcement goes to.\n\n### The sent announcements list\n\nThe **Announcements** tab lists everything you have sent, newest first. Each row shows its **Title**, how urgent it is, who it went to, **Sent By** (who sent it), **Sent** (date and time), and **Acks** — how many people have confirmed it. New announcements appear at the top on their own, even ones a colleague sends while you are looking at the list.\n\n### Seeing who confirmed\n\nClick any row (or the eye icon on it) to see who confirmed. It shows how many people have confirmed, a note if confirmation was required, and each person who confirmed with the date and time they did. If the announcement did not require confirmation, the list simply shows anyone who chose to confirm. This is how you make sure an urgent notice actually reached the people who needed to see it.\n\n### Templates\n\nAnnouncements you send often (a monthly safety reminder, a maintenance-window notice) are worth saving as **templates**. Switch to the **Templates** tab and click **New Template** to create one with:\n\n- **Name** (required) — how the template shows up in the picker.\n- **Content** (required) — the default message.\n- **Default Severity** and **Default Scope** — the urgency and audience it starts with.\n- **Require Acknowledgment by Default** — whether it asks people to confirm.\n\nSaved templates appear in the Templates list and in the template picker in the send window. To remove one, click the **trash** icon on its row and confirm — this is permanent, but it does not affect announcements already sent from it.\n\n### Severity, confirmation, and expiry at a glance\n\n- **Severity** is only a signal of urgency and the label color — it does not change who gets it.\n- **Require Acknowledgment** is what makes the Acks count and the who-confirmed list meaningful — without it, people simply read the banner.\n- **Expires At** stops the announcement from showing after the date; it does not delete the record, so it still appears in the sent list and you can still see who confirmed.","sections":[]}"""
